# ROCEV + Todo Loop

This repo's development contract (root `AGENTS.md`) applies inside Cursor too:
work is declared as obligations, closed with evidence, judged by validators.

For hardware flows, the spine is per stage:

```text
Requirement â†’ Obligation â†’ Contract â†’ Evidence â†’ Validation
req           (VCM todos)   SSOT/goals  artifacts   stage gates
```

- Full chain runs: use the `rocev-chain` skill (req â†’ rtl â†’ tb â†’ sim) or the
  `/rocev-chain` subagent. Single stages: `/req-gen`, `/rtl-gen`,
  `/tb-gen`, `/sim`.
- **Track todos in the external file the hook reads** â€” manage them via
  `python3 .cursor/scripts/cursor_todo.py {add|start|done|cancel|list|status}`,
  which writes `current_todos.json`. This file (NOT Cursor's internal todo UI) is
  the single source of "done"; the `stop` hook (`stop-todo-loop.py`) reads it and
  re-prompts while any todo stays open. Plan a stage â†’ `add` its todos â†’ `start`
  one â†’ attach the gate verdict as evidence â†’ `done`. The loop ends only when
  every todo is closed; never mark done without the validator output.
- Platform (core/src/lib) feature work additionally follows
  `ontology/platform_requirements.yaml` â€” declare an obligation before coding,
  flip it closed with a pytest node as evidence
  (`python3 scripts/platform_ontology.py check` must PASS before merge).
